\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
21 Lockhart IV is a rather unassuming name for what would prove to be one
 of the bloodiest battlefields of the entire Saurian War.
 A humid quagmire of jungles and swamps punctuated by wide rivers and open
 fields of 2-meter tall grasses, the planet was also ripe with rare earth
 metals vital for construction of new fusion drives and energy weapons,
 and smack in the middle of a major space lane for both Alliance and Saurian
 forces.
 Sent into the planet's harsh jungles to attempt to oust the Saurian colony,
 Alliance ground troops dubbed the world by another name: Paradise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Caught in the midst of this endless fighting were the Llorrai (singular:
 
\emph on
