 A mix of agrarian and hunter-gatherer tribes, the Llorrai were only barely
 on the cusp of civilization when the Saurian Empire settled on the planet.
 The occupying Saurian forces quickly set the capyfolk beneath their scaly
 heel, taking over farms and enslaving laborers for mining and manufacturing
 work.
 Unrest grew, and soon many Llorrai took up arms, stealing weapons and taking
 advantage of their experience with the local terrain to stymie Saurian
 troops.
 By the time the Alliance invaded, Paradise was already on the verge of
 a full civil war, and the human forces initially found the Llorrai guerillas
 to be as much trouble as the Saurians.
 Alliance troops would seize Saurian outposts only to find themselves under
 attack from behind the lines by Llorrai jungle fighters they'd simply never
 seen.
 Soldiers on both sides of the conflict told ghost stories about the Llorrai
 
