\begin_layout Subsection
Special Abilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\series bold
Armored Shell
\series default
: The external shell of the robot is designed to recieve considerable punishment
 without resultant damage to it's internals.
 All S.T.E.V.E.s have AC5 by default and ignore the first 2 points of any damage
 taken, but cannot equip other armor.
 In addition, their shell protects them from extremes of temperature from
 -200 to +600 degrees F.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\series bold
Robotic Metabolism
\series default
: As a robot, S.T.E.V.E.
 has no need to breathe and thus is impervious to the effects of atmosphere,
 but it does need to 'eat', in a manner of speaking.
 S.T.E.V.E.
 units must consume at least 1 pound of organic or synthetic hydrocarbons
 per week in order to fuel their interal power systems.
 This can be oil, petroleum, alcohol, meat or vegetable matter, or even
 coal.
 Failure to fuel the robot will force it to rely on reserve power, incurring
 a -1 penalty to all stats and to-hit values for the next week.
 After two weeks without fuel, the robot will shut down until it can be
 refueled.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\series bold
Adaptive Interface
\series default
: One of the robot's fingers contains a retractable tip that serves as a
 universal adapter for most electronic or computerized machinery and systems.
 This enables S.T.E.V.E.
 to communicate directly with a given computer or machine, giving it a +1
 to checks involving such systems, and a +1 to-hit with guided or ship-mounted
 weapon systems.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\noindent

\series bold
Plasma Tool
\series default
: Concealed within the right arm of the robot is a multi-purpose plasma
 tool capable of cutting, soldering and welding.
 In welding mode, the tool grants the robot a +1 to ship repair rolls, and
 in combat can be used to repair 1d3 Hull or 1d4 Armor.
 In soldering mode, the tool grants a +1 to repairing or rewiring electronics.
 In cutting mode, the tool can be used as a melee weapon that deals 2d10H
 damage, and can cut through metal and other materials given sufficient
 time (see 
\emph on
cutting torch, 
\emph default
H&H p.32).
 The plasma tool has a limited battery separate from the main power system
 of the robot, however, which holds 8 charges.
 Each use of the tool uses 1 charge, and the battery will only recharge
 after 8 hours without use.
\end_layout

