\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Service Service robots are those designed primarily for background roles
 as maintenance, customer service, diplomatic, or clerical work, and are
 usually humanoid in shape and appearance.
 Their light weight however does make them tuneable for agility, and this
 also makes service frames a popular choice for adapting into inflitration
 or stealth oriented combat robots.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Multi-Role Multi-role frames are the workhorses of the robot world, sturdy
 and durable enough to work in a wide range of conditions, but still light
 enough to avoid hampered mobility or practicality.
