\emph on
H&H 
\emph default
p.20), but also makes the robot fully susceptible to psychic and mental attacks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Bloodhound An advanced chemical sniffer installed in the robot's sensory
 apparatus allows it to instantly detect the atmospheric composition of
 a room, detect toxic substances, and even identify trace chemical trails
 left by living organisms.
 They have a +1 to WIS checks involving smell, and on a successful WIS check,
 the robot can track such trails to their source provided they are no more
 than a week old.
