\begin_layout Standard
As non-biological lifeforms constructed from various synthetic polymers
 and aerospace allows, a robot cannot heal itself naturally, nor can it
 be healed with standard medicinal substances and procedures.
 Instead, the robot must be repaired in order to remove damage.
 Field repair requires access to scrap parts and tools, and the robot cannot
 operate on itself.
 On a successful INT check, 1d6 damage can be repaired to the robot given
 access to sufficient scrap.
 
\end_layout

